      <section id="id1168700401313">
        <title>[LO 1.3]</title>
        <para id="id4669817">Draw parallel vertical lines in each frame. Indicate with an arrow the direction in which you draw the lines most easily.</para>
        <figure id="id7647247">
          <media id="id7647247_media" alt="">
            <image mime-type="image/png" src="../../media/graphics2-6f90.png" id="id7647247__onlineimage" height="304" width="634"/>
          </media>
        </figure>
        <para id="id2610931">Interesting:</para>
        <para id="id1168698143837">How do most right-handed learners draw the lines most easily?</para>
        <para id="id4900082">How do most left-handed learners draw the lines most easily?</para>
        <para id="id1168693996132"/>
        <para id="id1168688128489"><figure id="id1168689416204"><media id="id1168689416204_media" alt=""><image mime-type="image/png" src="../../media/graphics3-4af4.png" id="id1168689416204__onlineimage" height="178" width="213"/></media></figure>Background:</para>
        <para id="id8762590">Once you are able to draw horizontal and vertical lines, you must try to draw RIGHT ANGLES.</para>
