      <section id="id1168701941017">
        <title>[LO 1.3]</title>
        <para id="id8670536">Draw at least five triangles of different sizes. Experiment with the size of the angles.</para>
        <para id="id7318742">Background:</para>
        <para id="id7878795">The above-mentioned exercise is very important, since most of the objects that you will want to draw can be simplified and drawn as basic geometric figures. Therefore, in drawing a specific object you can use the geometric figures to form the framework.</para>
        <para id="id1168687961446">Make a drawing of an object such as an animal by using an oval that developed from a rectangle</para>
        <figure id="id1168701748220">
          <media id="id1168701748220_media" alt="">
            <image mime-type="image/png" src="../../media/graphics5-2777.png" id="id1168701748220__onlineimage" height="151" width="511"/>
          </media>
        </figure>
        <para id="id1168701882872">Let us practise drawing an oval or a circle with the aid of a square or a rectangle.</para>
        <para id="id1168702888165"><emphasis effect="bold">INSTRUCTIONS FOR A CIRCLE</emphasis>: </para>
        <list id="id1168701627272" list-type="enumerated" number-style="arabic">
          <item>Draw a square as in Assignment 5A. </item>
          <item>Mark half of each side with a small mark.</item>
          <item>Join the marks with a slight curve in order to form a circle.</item>
          <item>Draw the circle with a dark pencil.</item>
          <item>Erase the lines of the square carefully.</item>
        </list>
        <para id="id7798954"/>
      </section>
